# Trivy ignore file for known false positives and accepted risks
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# zlib/minizip: integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 — Debian does not build
# the vulnerable minizip code into its zlib binary packages (Debian status: ignored)
CVE-2023-45853 exp:2026-08-31

# glibc: integer overflow in memalign — Debian bookworm marks as <no-dsa>
# (minor issue, requires attacker control of size+alignment args)
CVE-2026-0861 exp:2026-08-31

# ── Rust crates embedded in compiled Polars .so (multiqc dependency) ──
# These live inside multiqc's prebuilt _polars_runtime.abi3.so; the fix requires
# Polars to release a build against the patched crate and multiqc to pull it, so
# no yml pin can reach the fix. Re-eval when multiqc ships a Polars with the fixes.
# quinn-proto: QUIC protocol DoS
# No fix available until Polars releases a build with quinn-proto >= 0.11.14
CVE-2026-31812 exp:2026-09-30
# rustls-webpki: DoS via panic on malformed CRL BIT STRING.
# No fix available until Polars releases a build with rustls-webpki >= 0.103.13.
GHSA-82j2-j2ch-gfr8 exp:2026-09-30
# pyo3: out-of-bounds read in nth/nth_back for PyList/PyTuple iterators via
# unchecked index+n overflow (HIGH); fixed in pyo3 >= 0.29.0. Reachable only if
# Polars runs those iterators over attacker-controlled n; multiqc feeds Polars its
# own pipeline QC dataframes, not untrusted iterator offsets.
GHSA-36hh-v3qg-5jq4 exp:2026-09-30

# linux-pam: directory traversal (no Debian fix available as of 2026-03-14)
CVE-2025-6020 exp:2026-08-31

# GnuPG gpgv: information disclosure / potential code execution (no Debian fix available as of 2026-03-14)
CVE-2025-68973 exp:2026-08-31

# ── Go stdlib v1.23.4 in ncbi-datasets-cli 18.21.0 (ncbi_datasets container) ──
# The NCBI datasets/dataformat binaries are pre-compiled Go executables distributed
# via conda-forge. They ship Go stdlib v1.23.4.
# Go ~= 1.25.11 or ~= 1.26.4 is required to address all vulnerabilities.
# We cannot rebuild these — only NCBI can, by updating their Go toolchain.
#
# Risk assessment: these binaries run in an isolated container that only downloads
# genome metadata from NCBI's API and writes local files. They do not serve TLS,
# connect to Postgres, or process untrusted archives — so the practical attack
# surface for these CVEs is minimal in our pipeline context.
#
# TODO: Remove these ignores when a newer ncbi-datasets-cli is available on
# conda-forge built with Go ~= 1.25.11 or ~= 1.26.4. Check with:
#   conda search -c conda-forge ncbi-datasets-cli
#   strings $(conda run -n <env> which datasets) | grep '^go1\.'
# As of 2026-06-04, 18.29.1 is the latest conda-forge build; its embedded Go
# version is unverified — the feedstock repackages NCBI's prebuilt binaries, so
# the Go toolchain is whatever NCBI shipped, not something conda-forge controls.
#
# crypto/tls: unexpected session resumption (CRITICAL)
CVE-2025-68121 exp:2026-09-30
# database/sql: Postgres scan race condition (HIGH)
CVE-2025-47907 exp:2026-09-30
# archive/tar: unbounded allocation parsing GNU sparse map (HIGH)
CVE-2025-58183 exp:2026-09-30
# net/url: memory exhaustion in query parameter parsing (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61726 exp:2026-09-30
# archive/zip: excessive CPU consumption building archive index (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61728 exp:2026-09-30
# crypto/x509: DoS via crafted certificate (HIGH)
CVE-2025-61729 exp:2026-09-30
# net/url: incorrect parsing of IPv6 host literals (HIGH)
CVE-2026-25679 exp:2026-09-30
# crypto/x509: DoS via excessive processing of DNS SAN entries in a crafted
# certificate (HIGH); these binaries validate only NCBI/AWS server certs.
CVE-2026-27145 exp:2026-09-30
# crypto/x509: excessive CPU in certificate chain building (HIGH)
CVE-2026-32280 exp:2026-09-30
# internal/syscall/unix: Root.Chmod can follow symlinks out of the root (HIGH)
CVE-2026-32282 exp:2026-09-30
# crypto/x509: DoS via inefficient certificate chain validation (HIGH)
CVE-2026-32281 exp:2026-09-30
# crypto/tls: TLS 1.3 post-handshake key-update deadlock DoS (HIGH)
CVE-2026-32283 exp:2026-09-30
# net (cgo resolver): LookupCNAME mishandling of overlong CNAME responses (HIGH)
CVE-2026-33811 exp:2026-09-30
# net/http: HTTP/2 transport infinite loop on crafted SETTINGS frames (HIGH)
CVE-2026-33814 exp:2026-09-30
# net/mail: DoS via crafted ParseAddress/ParseAddressList/ParseDate inputs (HIGH)
CVE-2026-39820 exp:2026-09-30
# net: panic in Dial/LookupPort when handling NUL byte (HIGH)
CVE-2026-39836 exp:2026-09-30
# net/mail: DoS via pathological consumePhrase inputs (HIGH)
CVE-2026-42499 exp:2026-09-30
# html/template: XSS via meta-content URL escaping bypass (HIGH); server-side
# templating, never used by these client-only metadata-download binaries.
CVE-2026-39823 exp:2026-09-30
# net/http/httputil: ReverseProxy query smuggling past urlmaxqueryparams (HIGH);
# these binaries are HTTP clients, run no reverse proxy.
CVE-2026-39825 exp:2026-09-30
# html/template: XSS via script type-attribute escaper bypass (HIGH); as above,
