CVE-2026-39826 exp:2026-09-30
# mime/net-mail: excessive CPU decoding crafted MIME headers with many invalid
# encoded-words (HIGH); these CLIs fetch JSON from NCBI's API, never parse email/MIME.
CVE-2026-42504 exp:2026-09-30

# ── Pillow in multiqc container (transitive dependency via matplotlib) ──
# multiqc 1.33 (latest on bioconda) pulls Pillow 12.1.1; fix requires >= 12.2.0.
# We cannot pin Pillow independently in the conda environment spec.
# The vulnerability is a FITS GZIP decompression bomb — not a realistic attack
# vector since multiqc only processes pipeline QC data, not untrusted FITS images.
CVE-2026-40192 exp:2026-09-30
# OOB write via integer overflow in PSD tile extents (HIGH): pipeline does not
# generate or process PSD-format images.
CVE-2026-42311 exp:2026-09-30

# ── Debian trixie base image (mambaorg/micromamba): no fixes reachable ──
# The base-image knob (container-base-image in pyproject.toml) is the only
# permitted lever for these system packages, and the current latest micromamba
# digest still ships the vulnerable versions — the fixes are not yet installed
# in any published base layer. Re-eval when micromamba rebuilds against a trixie
# apt state carrying the fix (then bump the digest and drop the entry).
#
# glibc: DoS via iconv() with specific character set conversions (fix_deferred)
# Our containers don't perform attacker-controlled iconv conversions.
CVE-2026-4046 exp:2026-08-31

# ncurses: stack-based buffer overflow in infocmp CLI tool (no-dsa, low urgency)
# Our containers never invoke infocmp. Fix only in sid (6.6+).
CVE-2025-69720 exp:2026-08-31

# openssl (libssl3t64, openssl-provider-legacy): use-after-free in PKCS7_verify()
# on crafted PKCS#7 / S/MIME messages with an empty digestAlgorithms field
# (HIGH, DSA-6335-1). Fixed in Debian trixie 3.5.6-1~deb13u2, but the container
# Dockerfile installs only `procps` (no apt upgrade) so openssl comes straight
# from the base layer, and no published micromamba digest carries deb13u2 yet —
# so the fix is not reachable via the permitted base-image bump. Applications
# using CMS APIs are unaffected; the pipeline verifies no PKCS#7/S-MIME signatures
# (openssl is linked only for TLS to known NCBI/AWS endpoints via curl/python).
# Re-eval: a micromamba rebuild ships deb13u2 (bump the digest and drop this).
CVE-2026-45447 exp:2026-08-31

# acl (libacl1) / attr (libattr1): symlink-traversal local privilege escalation
# in the acl_*_file() functions and getfattr/setfattr utilities (HIGH). Fixed only
# in Debian sid (acl 2.4.0-1, attr 1:2.6.0-1); trixie awaits a point release, so
# no base-image digest carries the fix yet. The pipeline never invokes getfattr/
# setfattr or the pathname-based libacl APIs, and containers run as root — outside
# the non-root local-attacker threat model. Re-eval: trixie point release / a
# micromamba rebuild that carries it.
CVE-2026-54369 exp:2026-08-31
CVE-2026-54371 exp:2026-08-31

# systemd: IPC API mishandling from unprivileged callers causing service freeze
# Our containers don't run systemd services. Fix only in sid (260.1+).
CVE-2026-29111 exp:2026-08-31

# libgcrypt20: heap overflow / DoS via crafted ECDH ciphertext to gcry_pk_decrypt
# (no Debian fix available as of 2026-04-29; fixed in upstream libgcrypt >= 1.12.2)
# Our pipeline containers never decrypt attacker-controlled ECDH ciphertext.
# Check for a Debian fix at:
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-41989
CVE-2026-41989 exp:2026-08-31

# libcap2: setcap (cap_set_file) exploit usable by non-root users.
# (No Debian fix available as of 2026-05-01.) Our pipeline containers do
# not invoke setcap/cap_set_file, so we do not call the affected code;
# additionally, they run as root, which puts them outside the non-root
# threat model of this CVE.
# Check for a Debian fix at:
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-4878
CVE-2026-4878 exp:2026-08-31

# ── urllib3 2.6.3 transitive via awscli=2.34.9 in blast, bowtie2_samtools,
# kraken2, minimap2_samtools ──
# Our awscli usage is `update_blastdb.pl --source aws` and equivalents — HTTPS
# to known NCBI/AWS endpoints, no proxy, no attacker-controlled compressed
# streams; neither CVE is reachable. Fix exists in urllib3>=2.7.0 but every
# current conda-forge awscli build pins urllib3<=2.6.3; re-eval when the
# feedstock relaxes the cap.
# CVE-2026-44431 (HIGH): cross-origin header leak in proxied low-level redirects.
CVE-2026-44431 exp:2026-09-30
# CVE-2026-44432 (HIGH): decompression-bomb safeguard bypass in streaming reads.
CVE-2026-44432 exp:2026-09-30

# ── perl-base (Debian trixie 5.40.1-6): no fixed version available as of 2026-06-04 ──
# The pipeline's only perl invocation is `update_blastdb.pl` in the maintainer-run
# INDEX step (modules/local/downloadBlastDB), which fetches official NCBI/AWS BLAST
# databases via `--source aws`. perl-base is otherwise present only as a Debian
# base-image dependency, not called by any pipeline tool. None of these CVEs is
# reachable on attacker-controlled input in that context. Re-eval: Debian backports
# a fix to trixie perl-base (a rebuild then clears them), or the pipeline gains a
# perl path that processes untrusted tar/regex/glob input.
# Archive::Tar symlink path traversal on extraction (CRITICAL); BLAST DB tarballs are trusted.
CVE-2026-42496 exp:2026-08-31
# perl regex compiler (Perl_study_chunk) heap overflow (CRITICAL); no attacker-controlled regex is compiled.
CVE-2026-8376 exp:2026-08-31
# Archive::Tar hardlink path traversal on extraction (HIGH); same trusted-tarball-only exposure as CVE-2026-42496.
CVE-2026-42497 exp:2026-08-31
# IO::Compress/File::GlobMapper eval-string injection via output glob (HIGH); no attacker-controlled glob.
CVE-2026-48962 exp:2026-08-31
# Archive::Tar unbounded allocation -> memory-exhaustion DoS (HIGH); trusted tarballs, worst case ephemeral OOM.
CVE-2026-9538 exp:2026-08-31
